The Federal Executive Council has approved N185.2 billion for the construction and rehabilitation of 14 road projects in different parts of the country. Presidential spokesman Femi Adesina disclosed this to State House correspondents after the five-hour cabinet meeting presided over by President Muhammmadu Buhari. Adesina, who spoke on behalf of the Minister of Power, Works and Housing, Babatunde Fashola, listed the projects thus: Gwoza - Damboa - Goniri - Ngamdu Road in Yobe/Borno States by Hajaig Construction Nigeria Ltd. at the cost of N34.608bn. Mayo Belwa - Jada - Ganye - Torngo Road in Adamawa by Messrs Triacta Nigeria Ltd. at the rate of N22.699bn. Ado - Ifaki - Otun - Kwara State border in Ekiti State at the rate of N6.002bn. Repair Makurdi bridge in Benue State by Messrs AG VisioÂ  Construction Ltd.N4.617bn. Ihugi - Korinya -Wuse -Ankor in Benue State Datum Construction Ltd N15.641bn. Gbagi - Apa - Owode in Badagry Lagos State by Messrs Smithcrown Nigeria Ltd.at NN4.366bn. Construction Ijebu Igbo - Ita Egba Owonowen in Ogun and Oyo Statesto Messrs DC EngineeringN9.833bn. Dualisation of Jattu - Fugar - Agenebode in Edo Phase II by Mothercat at N7.506bn. Makurdi - Gboko - Wannune - Yander Section 1 in Benue State to Messrs Rockbridge Construction Ltd. at the rate of N18.669bn. Old - Enugu - Port Harcourt Road at Agbogugu - Abia border Spur by Messrs Setraco Ltd. at N13.933bn. Rehabilitation of Umulungbe - Umoka road at N6.249bn. Amokwu - Ikedimkpe - Egede - Opeyi Awhum Road in Enugu State to Messrs IDC Construction N21.729bn. Rehabilitation of Nkwu Inyi - Akpugoeze in Anambra State Anbeez Services at N2.595bn. Construction of Sabon Birnin - Tsululu - Kuya - Maradi Junction road in Sokoto by Messrs China Zhonghao Nigeria Ltd N4.354bn.